    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-11-20T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-11-20T12:00:00-05:00" n="555"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d555">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.154/366: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in El Salvador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Curtis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San Salvador</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-11-20T11:00:00-06:00"
                            >November 20, 1931—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 1 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>94. Referring to Department’s instruction No. 203 of October 15,<note n="45"
                        xml:id="d555fn45">See footnote 44a, <ref target="#pg_712">p.
                        712</ref>.</note> the President informs me orally that the Salvadoran
                    Government agrees gladly to the aerial survey.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Curtis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
